title: For Sale:  SCAMS on Eau Claire Armslist
postcontent:
I can guarantee with no doubt that the following ads are scams.

Thursday August 1st

For Sale: Colt Python .357 nickel 6 inch

For Sale: Desert Eagle 50AE Brushed Chrome

Both of these ads were up here before, same pic and no pic, same language, no number. 

They informed me they are not in Eau Claire but in Pennsylvania and need personal info and payment if you wish to proceed. The ads are obvious scams. A Python in new condition? A Desert Eagle brushed stainless for 900? I don't think so. 

Here are the replies I got.

"Yes it is still available and it is clean and functions well
where are you located?"
"Am in Pennsylvania, how would you like to proceed? price includes shipping to your FFL,do you have an FFL dealer that you  work with?"

These are replies to my detailed questions which were never answered, obviously suspicious. 

a scam alert in another state on armslist for this same scammer is in pic

Many of Thursday's ads look like scams to me, but I know these two are. Be careful and if you are a legit seller use a phone number as a contact, it at least gives the impression you are real. 

I WILL NO LONGER BE RESPONDING TO ADS WHO DO NOT PROVIDE PHONE NUMBER.

postcontent: Vintage Klipsch KG-4 Stereo Speakers  with Oak Finished Cabinets.   The Klipsch KG4 speaker system provides 100 watts of continuous power per channel; each speaker has a maximum power of 500 watts. The speakers have a nominal impedance of 6 ohms, lower than the 8 ohms standard on most speaker systems; this means that these speakers may draw more power from their source and put out more wattage per signal. It is recommended that you check the compatibility of your stereo device with a 6-ohm impedance speaker. The Klipsch KG4 speakers have a frequency range of 38-20,000 Hz, offering close to the full range of human hearing. The Klipsch KG4 speakers are each fitted with a tweeter and two woofer diaphragms set in a medium-density fiberboard enclosure. The woofers are each 8 inches and the tweeter is 1 inch. The speakers have a two-way design, meaning that input signals are split so that the low frequencies are routed through the woofer while the high frequencies are routed through the tweeter. This ensures that the sound will provide as close to a full and equal range as possible. Read more: http://www.ehow.com/info_8211458_klipsch-kg4-specs.html#ixzz2ZRRzovWn Make an appointment to audition, They sound awesome.

It shoots WAY better than I do and is what all other 1911's strive to be in a 45! 

This gun has either ridden on my side or has been kept top shelf in my gun safe. It has been well cared for, never been dropped or abused, but does show the typical signs of holster wear. Though it is not new, it is in excellent condition. I have had it completely stripped, examined, lubed and appraised by a local and well respected gunsmith of 20 something years in the field. I have a written appraisal detailing his evaluation that I will post and include with the gun.

I am selling this as a package deal, but if you see something you like, I would be willing to split a few items, but want to include at least one holster and 2 mags with the gun. I would consider a trade plus cash on your end for a NIB or near new GLOCK 30S only at this time. There are other guns I am wanting at this time, but I also need some cash for life expenses right now. 

I've posted some pics here, but have many more that I can email or text any other pics that you may need of this gun. FTF deals or shipping to your FFL dealer for additional $25; insured extra. Feel free to contact me with any questions. 

This is a TOP OF THE LINE 1911 - if you want the best of the best 1911 in a complete conceal carry package, you will not do any better. I can not state enough HOW COMFORTABLE the Milt Sparks Versa Max II holster carries! The mag holster carries the mag as close and high on your belt as I've ever seen in a mag holster!

This rifle was made in 1916, and this model was made from 1914-1917.
